Let $f(x)$ be a twice continuously differentiable in the interval $(0, infinity)$. If

$ lim_(x -> infinity) (x^2 f''(x) + 4x f'(x) + 2 f(x)) = 1, $

find $display(lim_(x -> infinity) f(x))$ and $display(lim_(x -> infinity) x f'(x))$.
Do bold(not) assume any special form of $f(x)$. Hint: use l'Hôpital's rule.
